UNITED STATES of America ex rel. HOM LEE HONG, Next Friend of Hom Sang, Appellant, v. CHINESE INSPECTOR IN CHARGE AT THE PORT OF NEW YORK, etc., Appellee. No. 384. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. April 20, 1931. James C. Thomas, of New York City, for appellant. George Z. Medalie, U. S. Atty., of New York City (Walter H. Schulman, Asst. U. S. Atty., of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before L. HAND, SWAN, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Order affirmed.
